    "introduction": "Shauna is an Irish-Canadian film, TV, voice and theatre actor with theatre credits across Canada and the US. Notable theatres performed at include several years at The Shaw Festival, The Stratford Festival, and home of the Fighting Irish - Notre Dame University. She is a graduate of the prestigious Birmingham Conservatory at the Stratford Festival, where she currently owns a farmhouse older than the country of Canada. Send help. Shauna is the benevolent yet fierce commissioner of the the only All-Women, All-Canadian fantasy football league. Her dominance in many fantasy leagues has led her to be interviewed by Matthew Berry on ESPN. She is also a former competitive gymnast and Champion-level Irish dancer, in which she qualified for the World's Championships at age 11. The greatest love of her life is her heinz 57 pound-pup senior, Juliet. Adopt don't shop!",
